Citations
Date: 20/5/1933
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 263
Edition:
Quote: Scirpus maritimus, the tall leafy swamp plant that favours salty estuarial situations which are subject to periodical flooding is known to the Maoris of the Northern estuaries as 'purua grass', cattle browsing it readily when allowed.
